description.narrative: In 2020, YCO faced significant resource mobilization challenges, with the constrained humanitarian space and shift in donor behavior shaping much of the 2020 funding landscape. While YCO mobilized adequate funding for the Country Programme, it was uneven across the sectors and also between humanitarian and non-humanitarian funding. Despite funding challenges, the resources mobilized in 2020 enabled UNICEF to respond to the humanitarian needs in Yemen as well as support and build on longer term investments in systems strengthening and development interventions. | Status:Partially met | As-of Date:17/01/2021
